properties.headline: Flood Warning issued February 6 at 9:36AM EST until February 7 at 6:30AM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Florida...

Alafia River At Riverview near US 301

.Strong southerly winds and moderate to heavy rainfall today and
tonight will lead to water rises in Tampa Bay. As a result, discharge
from the Alafia River at Riverview near US 301, coupled with additional
water in the bay will lead to the possibility of brief flooding at
high tide tonight. The waters are expected to quickly fall below flood
stage by early Friday morning.

The Flood Warning continues for
The Alafia River At Riverview near US 301
* From tonight through Friday morning.
* At 09 AM Thursday the stage was 0.3 feet.
* Minor flooding is forecast at 4.6 feet at 11 pm.
* Flood stage is 4.2 feet.
* Impact...at 4.2 feet...Water begins to impact homes on Pine Avenue
and Park Drive.
* Flood history...This compares to a previous crest of 4.6 feet
on Jun 6 2016.
properties.instruction:
Do not drive cars through flooded areas.

Stay tuned to developments by listening to NOAA Weather Radio. The
latest forecasts can also be found on weather.gov/tampabay. You can
follow NWSTampaBay on Twitter and like us on Facebook.
